🌍 Real-World Scenario
Imagine:
A fintech platform processes payments asynchronously.
When a user makes a payment:
	1. API service publishes PaymentInitiated event.
	2. Fraud service consumes event.
	3. Ledger service updates balance.
	4. Notification service sends confirmation.
	5. Analytics service records metrics.
All via an event bus (e.g., Apache Kafka).
Modern systems are async-first because:
	• Loose coupling
	• Scalability
	• Resilience
	• Independent service deployment
But async introduces new attack surfaces.

